==Pre-season==
On 1 August 1970, Paris Saint-Germain opened their preseason campaign with a friendly match against [[US Quevilly|Quevilly]] at the [[Stade Jean-Bouin]]. The fixture became the first game played and the first defeat under the new name, "Paris Saint-Germain Football Club". The match saw the logic triumph of Quevilly by marker of 2-1. Under the view of 2,000 spectators and with the presence of then [[France national football team]] manager, [[Georges Boulogne]], [[Jean-Claude Bras]] scored the capital club's only goal before the half-time and first in the history for Paris Saint-Germain in a friendly match.<ref name="pmp">{{cite news
| title = 1er aoÃ»t 1970, le premier match du PSG
| url = http://www.psg.fr/fr/40-ans/900108/40ans-Article/49677/1er-aout-1970-le-premier-match-du-PSG
| work = PSG.fr
| accessdate = 29 September 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news 
| title = PSG-Quevilly, une longue histoire
| url = http://www.psg.fr/fr/40-ans/900108/40ans-Article/48440/PSG-Quevilly-une-longue-histoire
| work = PSG.fr
| accessdate = 7 July 2010}}</ref> After the victory over Quevilly, the capital club continued its preparations for the coming season against Fontainebleau. The match ended in a 1-1 draw and Bernard BÃ©reau scored PSG's only goal.<ref name="s70"/> 
