==Division 2==
Paris Saint-Germain began their league campaign on the road taking on [[Poitiers FC|Poitiers]] at the [[Stade de la PÃ©piniÃ¨re]] in the first day of the [[1970â71 French Division 2|1970â71 Division 2]]. The fixture ended in a 1-1 draw and Bernard Guignedoux scored the capital club's first goal in its first official match.<ref name="pmp"/> On 20 September, Michel Prost became PSG's first player to score a brace as the capital club defeated [[Stade Malherbe Caen|Caen]]. On 25 October, [[LB ChÃ¢teauroux|ChÃ¢teauroux]] became the first club to beat Paris Saint Germain after the match ended in a comprehensive 0-2 victory at the [[Parc des Princes]]. On 1 May 1971, the club's match against [[Quimper Cornouaille FC|Quimper]] was interrupted after only 22 minutes of play following a breakdown of lighting. The game, in which PSG led 1-0, was replayed on 2 April and ended in a 1-1 draw. Two days later, [[ÃDS MontluÃ§on|MontluÃ§on]] became the second and last club to defeat "Les Parisiens" during this campaign. On 15 May, PSG needed only a draw in their visit to [[FC Rouen|Rouen]] for gaining promotion to the first division. Encouraged by 5,000 fans who made the trip, the capital club recorded a 1-3 victory over "Les Diables Rouges", finishing first in Group B, securing their rise to the [[Ligue 1|Division 1]], and qualifying for the Division 2 title playoff.<ref name="s70"/> 

