==Title Playoff==
The Division 2 format was designed to award the title and the winners of each group had to meet on a single match, with the best being crowned champion. On 6 June 1971, Paris Saint-Germain recorded a 2-2 draw in the first playoff match against the winner of Group C, [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]]. A week later, "Les Parisiens" were crowned champions after achieving a 4-1 victory against Group A winners [[Lille OSC|Lille]] in the second playoff match. Paris Saint-Germain finished first with 4 points, while Monaco finished second with 2 points and Lille third with 1 point. The title was PSG's first in their short history.<ref name="s70"/> 

