==Coupe de France==
Paris Saint-Germain entered the [[1970â71 Coupe de France]] during the Fifth Round and was pitted against [[FC Dieppe|Dieppe]]. PSG recorded a narrow victory over Dieppe thanks to a goal from the top goalscorer Jacques RÃ©mond. After recording the club's first win in the French Cup, "Les Parisiens" will now take on Ãtaples at the [[Parc des Princes]] in the Sixth Round. Paris qualified for the last-64 of the French Cup with another narrow win over courageous Ãtaples. Bernard Guignedoux scored the only goal of the match. The draw for the Round of 64 of the French Cup was determined and Paris Saint-Germain were pitted against [[CS Louhans-Cuiseaux|Louhans-Cuiseaux]]. "Les Rouge-et-Bleu" were looking for a spot in the Round of 32, however, in a very close match, Paris Saint-Germain bowed out of the French Cup after being defeated 2-1 by the home side thanks to a brace from Jean Girardot. [[Jean-Pierre Destrumelle]] scored the only goal of the capital outfit in a match that became PSG's first defeat in the French Cup.<ref name="s70"/> 
